---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE, SITE_DESCRIPTION } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<h1>Dacular</h1>
			<p>
				Dacular is an experimental project to run a local AI agent stack on a Mac mini and expose
				it as a Claude skill anyone can install.
			</p>
			<p>The stack runs two systems locally:</p>
			<ul>
				<li><strong>zeroclaw</strong> — agent framework</li>
				<li><strong>Modular Max with Gemma3</strong> — local inference engine</li>
			</ul>
			<p>
				Install the <code>install-dacular</code> skill from the Claude skill marketplace to get a
				guided setup that wires everything together on your Mac mini.
			</p>
			<h2>How it works</h2>
			<ol>
				<li>A dedicated macOS account is created for the AI stack, isolated from your personal data.</li>
				<li>zeroclaw and Modular Max are installed into that account and configured to talk to each other.</li>
				<li>
					Before starting Claude, any data mount from the main account is removed — private data
					is never accessible while Claude is running.
				</li>
			</ol>
			<p><em>Mac mini only for now.</em></p>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
